92d3481\";a:11:{s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"website\";s:10:\"visibility\";s:6:\"public\";s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"University website\";s:3:\"url\";s:17:\"http://depaul.edu\";s:6:\"target\";s:4:\"same\";s:6:\"follow\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";s:1:\"5\";s:5:\"order\";i:1;s:9:\"preferred\";b:0;s:5:\"image\";b:0;s:4:\"logo\";b:1;}}','','','','<p class=\"p1\">The Department of Writing, Rhetoric, and Discourse (WRD), one of the largest departments at DePaul, is dedicated to studying the history and theory of literate activity and helping students excel as writers in a wide range of academic, professional, and public settings. Created July 1, 2007, WRD is home to three undergraduate programs:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>DePaul’s First-Year Writing program; the Minor in Professional Writing; and the Major in WRD.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>At the graduate level, the Master of Arts in WRD addresses writing in professional and technical contexts, the preparation of postsecondary teacher-scholars in writing, and the study of language for writers.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The department’s MA in New Media Studies prepares graduates to function as productive and responsible individuals in social contexts created by new media through both critical interpretation and situated practical activity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>WRD also offers two Combined BA/MA programs, which link the WRD BA with either graduate program and allow undergraduates to begin taking graduate courses in their senior year. WRD also offers a Graduate Certificate in TESOL.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">WRD is made up of more than 70 faculty members, all of whom teach at the undergraduate level.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The department’s Graduate Faculty comprises nationally recognized researchers in rhetorical theory and practice, composition theory, writing pedagogy, applied linguistics, second language writing, professional and technical writing, and writing program administration.</p>','','a:4:{s:5:\"entry\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:12:\"organization\";}s:5:\"group\";a:1:{s:6:\"family\";a:0:{}}s:4:\"logo\";a:4:{s:6:\"linked\";b:1;s:7:\"display\";b:1;s:4:\"name\";s:25:\"wordmark-full-bw-copy.jpg\";s:4:\"meta\";a:8:{s:4:\"name\";s:25:\"wordmark-full-bw-copy.jpg\";s:4:\"path\";s:118:\"/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/Web/iwdpa_home/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/depaul-university/wordmark-full-bw-copy.jpg\";s:3:\"url\";s:111:\"http://independentwriting.org/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/depaul-university/wordmark-full-bw-copy.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:225;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:4:\"size\";s:24:\"width=\"225\" height=\"150\"\";s:4:\"mime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:4:\"type\";i:2;}}s:5:\"image\";a:4:{s:6:\"linked\";b:1;s:7:\"display\";b:1;s:4:\"name\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";s:27:\"wordmark-full-bw-copy-1.jpg\";}s:4:\"meta\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";a:8:{s:4:\"name\";s:27:\"wordmark-full-bw-copy-1.jpg\";s:4:\"path\";s:120:\"/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/Web/iwdpa_home/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/depaul-university/wordmark-full-bw-copy-1.jpg\";s:3:\"url\";s:113:\"http://independentwriting.org/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/depaul-university/wordmark-full-bw-copy-1.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:225;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:4:\"size\";s:24:\"width=\"225\" height=\"150\"\";s:4:\"mime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:4:\"type\";i:2;}}}}',2,1,2,0,'approved'),(4,'2015-06-26 20:17:45','1435331242',0,'organization','public','morningside-college','','','','','','','','Morningside College','Department of Writing & Rhetoric','Leslie','Werden','a:1:{s:32:\"df185b3aa4e246b7a8732d6a2d84de55\";a:14:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"home\";s:10:\"visibility\";s:6:\"public\";s:6:\"line_1\";s:23:\"1501 Morningside Avenue\";s:6:\"line_2\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"line_3\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"city\";s:10:\"Sioux City\";s:5:\"state\";s:2:\"IA\";s:7:\"zipcode\";s:5:\"51106\";s:7:\"country\";s:3:\"USA\";s:8:\"latitude\";s:15:\"42.474615000000\";s:9:\"longitude\";s:16:\"-96.35970100000