full time, tenure-track professors in the department, each serving in a key WPA role: Director of First Year Writing, Director of Writing-Across-the-Curriculum, and Director of The Writing Center. The course offerings are First Year Experience (freshman seminar), Composition and Communication (second semester freshman writing), Basic Writing/Academic Reading, Persuasive Writing, and Advanced Public Speaking. Beginning Spring 2016, we will also offer a 300-level Topics Course in Rhetoric.</p>','','a:4:{s:5:\"entry\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:12:\"organization\";}s:5:\"group\";a:1:{s:6:\"family\";a:0:{}}s:4:\"logo\";a:4:{s:6:\"linked\";b:1;s:7:\"display\";b:1;s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Morningside2.png\";s:4:\"meta\";a:8:{s:4:\"name\";s:16:\"Morningside2.png\";s:4:\"path\";s:111:\"/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/Web/iwdpa_home/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/morningside-college/Morningside2.png\";s:3:\"url\";s:104:\"http://independentwriting.org/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/morningside-college/Morningside2.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:236;s:6:\"height\";i:147;s:4:\"size\";s:24:\"width=\"236\" height=\"147\"\";s:4:\"mime\";s:9:\"image/png\";s:4:\"type\";i:3;}}s:5:\"image\";a:4:{s:6:\"linked\";b:1;s:7:\"display\";b:1;s:4:\"name\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";s:18:\"Morningside2-1.png\";}s:4:\"meta\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";a:8:{s:4:\"name\";s:18:\"Morningside2-1.png\";s:4:\"path\";s:113:\"/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/Web/iwdpa_home/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/morningside-college/Morningside2-1.png\";s:3:\"url\";s:106:\"http://independentwriting.org/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/morningside-college/Morningside2-1.png\";s:5:\"width\";i:236;s:6:\"height\";i:147;s:4:\"size\";s:24:\"width=\"236\" height=\"147\"\";s:4:\"mime\";s:9:\"image/png\";s:4:\"type\";i:3;}}}}',2,2,2,0,'approved'),(5,'2015-08-25 03:44:20','1438133666',0,'organization','public','the-university-of-texas-at-san-antonio','','','','','','','','The University of Texas at San Antonio','The Writing Program','Gail','Pizzola'