s:5:\"order\";i:0;s:9:\"preferred\";b:0;s:5:\"image\";b:0;s:4:\"logo\";b:0;}}','','','','The Thompson Writing Program emerged in 2000 as an innovative program designed to teach writing to undergraduates from a multidisciplinary perspective. Our program now has four primary branches:\r\n\r\n<strong>First-Year Writing</strong>: Writing 101: Academic Writing is a one-semester, theme-based course taken during the first year by all Duke University undergraduate students and taught by full-time postdoctoral Fellows with Ph.D.s across disciplines.\r\n\r\n<strong>Writing Studio</strong>: The Writing Studio offers Duke University undergraduate and graduate students an opportunity to meet with trained writing tutors to discuss individual writing concerns.\r\n\r\n<strong>Writing in the Disciplines</strong>: The primary aim of the Writing in the Disciplines program is to support our faculty in all aspects of their work with student writing. This includes consulting on assignment design to developing new W-coded courses to offering workshops on giving feedback and grading.\r\n\r\n<strong>Faculty Write Program</strong>: The Faculty Write Program focuses on faculty-as-writers and aims to reinvigorate commitments to writing and teaching writing at Duke. The program cultivates multidisciplinary communities of writers to advance faculty writing and conversations about writing and research across the curriculum.','','a:3:{s:5:\"entry\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:12:\"organization\";}s:5:\"group\";a:1:{s:6:\"family\";a:0:{}}s:5:\"image\";a:4:{s:6:\"linked\";b:1;s:7:\"display\";b:1;s:4:\"name\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";s:28:\"DukeLogo-admin-ajax.php_.jpg\";}s:4:\"meta\";a:1:{s:8:\"original\";a:8:{s:4:\"name\";s:28:\"DukeLogo-admin-ajax.php_.jpg\";s:4:\"path\";s:119:\"/share/CACHEDEV1_DATA/Web/iwdpa_home/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/duke-university/DukeLogo-admin-ajax.php_.jpg\";s:3:\"url\";s:112:\"http://independentwriting.org/wp-content/uploads/connections-images/duke-university/DukeLog